
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `aspell` baraye dorost nevisi va tekrare kalemat dar file-haye matni (text files) estefade mishavad.  In dastoor mitavanad eshtebahat emlai ra peyda konad va pishnahadate dorost ra arayeh dahad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `aspell check <file>`  --> 📝 Check kardan yek file be tor dorost nevisi.
    🔹 `aspell list <file>`   --> 📜 List kardan hameye kalemat ghalat dar yek file.
    🔹 `aspell -d <dict> check <file>`  --> 📚 Estefade az yek dictionary khosoosi baraye check kardan.
    🔹 `aspell create <dict> ` --> 🔨 Sakhtan dictionary khosoosi.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ aspell check myfile.txt

    🔹 Check kardan file `myfile.txt` baraye eshtebahat emlai.

    $ aspell list myfile.txt

    🔹 List kardan kalemat ghalat dar file `myfile.txt`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ aspell check mydocument.txt
    ... (Output with suggestions) ...
    🔹 Ba ejraye in dastoor, `aspell` eshtebahate emlai ra dar `mydocument.txt` neshon midahad va pishnahadate dorost ra arayeh midahad. Shoma mitavanid kalemat ra dorost konid ya az pishnahadat estefade konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `aspell` command is used for spell checking and correcting words in text files.  It can find spelling errors and provide correct suggestions.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `aspell check <file>`  --> 📝 Check a file for spelling errors.
    🔹 `aspell list <file>`   --> 📜 List all misspelled words in a file.
    🔹 `aspell -d <dict> check <file>`  --> 📚 Use a custom dictionary for checking.
    🔹 `aspell create <dict> ` --> 🔨 Create a personal dictionary.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ aspell check myfile.txt

    🔹 Check the file `myfile.txt` for spelling mistakes.

    $ aspell list myfile.txt

    🔹 List the misspelled words in the file `myfile.txt`.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ aspell check mydocument.txt
    ... (Output with suggestions) ...
    🔹 By running this command, `aspell` will show spelling errors in `mydocument.txt` and provide corrections. You can correct the words or use the suggestions.
